dataIdInfo.idAbs: The dataset represents Soviet regions of Ukraine. DISCLAIMER: Admin3 "Bakhchysaraiskyi" and "Sevastopol" do not nest with the Admin2 layer.

Consts.useLimit: See the COD/FOD Registry Terms of Use. This does not replace any terms of use information provided with the dataset.

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was sent to ITOS in an email from UNOCHA. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following was found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Created and populated admin parent name and p-code fields. Attribution comes from p-code's parent p-code portions. 2. Admin3 name "Pereiaslavсska" with Cyrillic "с" was given Latin "c". 3. Found and fixed multipart sliver errors in "Ostrytska", "Odeska" and "Kamin-Kashyrska". 4. Admin3 "Vylkivska" had two features with duplicate p-code "UA5108001". These were combined into one multipart feature. 5. Fixed 73 small nesting errors between Admin0-3.
Users should be aware that: - 6 Admin3 names are not unique within their Admin2: Chornomorska, Kalininska, Leninska, Mykolaivska, Oktiabrska, Pokrovska - 45 Admin3 names do not have a 1 to 1 relationship between languages. - Admin3 "Bakhchysaraiskyi" and "Sevastopol" do not nest with the Admin2 layer.
